(firstQuint)Evaluation of 5 Days Holter and 30 Days Thumb-ECG for Detection of Atrial Fibrillation in Stroke Patients.

 Patients with a newly stroke will be examined with both 5 day holter monitoring and 30 days thumb ECG at the same time.

 The detection rates of the two methods will be compared.

